 :tx/rationale "DESIGN: Two-part fix for silent write failures. (1) Add --quiet/-q flag to all commands — suppresses M(t) guidance footer WITHOUT suppressing errors. Agents use '-q' instead of '2>/dev/null'. This separates guidance (optional) from errors (critical) on stderr. ~10 LOC: add global --quiet flag, skip footer when set. (2) Make 'braid task set' accept --title/--priority/--status/--type flags IN ADDITION TO positional args. Aligns with 'task create' syntax. Agents can transfer knowledge between commands. ~15 LOC: add Optional flag args to TaskAction::Set, prefer flags over positionals when both present. COMPOUND EFFECT: These two small changes would have prevented ALL 13 silent revision failures in this session. Every future session benefits."
